title: Inc. (the significant School) was incorporated in June 2015 as a not-for-profit corporation operated in accounting the District of Columbia. The School has officially opened its doors to students in policies August 2016 as a first-year academic public charter school. The mission is to eliminate the achievement gap in historically underserved communities
Notes to Financial Statements On October 31, 2015, the School entered into an instruction agreement with Apple Tree Institute for Education (Apple Tree), a District of Columbia organization
Per the terms of the agreement, Apple Tree will fully manage and operate the educational program for pre-school and pre-kindergarten (“Pre-K3” and “Pre-K4”
